My meme

This is a meme that encapsulates the honest feeling of someone who might be chronically online or just shy for real life meet ups, by showing a cat on a tiny computer saying how much it loves it because all its companions are on there show us why it loves it so much and also makes us pity it because it has no irl friends. 

library(magick)
library(tidyverse)

meme <- image_read("https://external-preview.redd.it/K84TkVVWuCkcT2Lm5XpfchCV59hx6MPUIiAXdfvCKHM.jpg?width=640&crop=smart&auto=webp&s=f4fefe5417936ac88116819c9b6098070f915cfd") %>% #first image
  image_append(image_scale(650)) %>% #size change
  image_annotate("I luv my puter!", size = 50, gravity = "north", color = "pink") %>% #top text
  image_annotate("All mah frens on there!", size = 50, gravity = "south", color = "pink") #bottom text

meme2 <- image_blank(650,50,"pink") # pink swuare that goes behind the meme to give more room

memefinal <- image_append(c(meme,meme2),stack = TRUE) %>% image_annotate("tiny puter haha",size = 15, gravity = "southwest", color = "white") #stacking together and adding extra text

memefinal #final product

image_write(memefinal,"My_meme.png") #export final

My animated GIF

This is a simple animation of a rat becoming french, by using a logo of ratatouille restaurant it explains the reason the rat is turning french since the movie took place in France.

france rat

library(magick)
rat1 <- image_scale(image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/466955797/photo/rat.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=Pou0phlNMe15VBZrzImJF541kmjHATPCRzHCAnwcMew=")) # the first image
rat2 <-  image_scale(image_read("https://mystickermania.com/cdn/stickers/cartoons/la-ratatoille-bistro-512x512.png")) # second image

animation <- image_resize(c(rat1,rat2),"300X300!") %>%
  image_background("white") %>%
  image_morph(frames = 16) %>%
  image_animate(optimize = TRUE) %>% 
  image_annotate("Becoming French", size = 25, gravity = "north",)

animation

image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
